WEBVTT

00:06.174 --> 00:07.676
ANNOUNCER:
Thanks for joining us...

00:07.676 --> 00:09.803
...at the Pro Bowlers' Annual
Christmas Tournament...

00:09.803 --> 00:12.806
...where some of the most incredible athletes
from around the country...

00:13.098 --> 00:15.558
...have gathered to compete
for the sport's biggest prize.

00:15.809 --> 00:16.935
Unh! Hey!

00:17.185 --> 00:18.728
[FEEDBACK OVER SPEAKERS]

00:19.813 --> 00:21.856
SPORTSMASTER:
Sport? Ha! Sport?

00:21.856 --> 00:25.735
Hey, news flash, people.
Bowling is not a sport.

00:25.735 --> 00:28.196
A real athlete deserves this prize money.

00:28.446 --> 00:31.700
Oh, but don't worry, I'm not gonna steal it.
I'm gonna win it.

00:36.997 --> 00:37.998
Hey.

00:39.833 --> 00:41.001
[BEEPING]

00:42.502 --> 00:43.586
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

00:43.837 --> 00:45.171
[MEN GASP]

00:51.553 --> 00:54.723
Sportsmaster.
Figures I'd find you in the gutters.

00:54.723 --> 00:57.934
I like to play fair, Batman,
but you're outnumbered.

00:58.184 --> 00:59.477
[THUG GRUNTS]

01:01.563 --> 01:04.733
Then it's a good thing
crime-fighting is a team sport.

01:05.483 --> 01:08.820
Okay, Beetle, Sportsmaster's mine.
You take the second-stringers.

01:08.820 --> 01:10.155
[SCARAB SPEAKS ALIEN LANGUAGE]

01:10.405 --> 01:13.366
Don't tell me what to do, goober.

01:13.700 --> 01:15.744
Oh, great. Now Batman thinks I'm a jerk.

01:15.744 --> 01:17.078
[SCARAB SPEAKS ALIEN LANGUAGE]

01:17.328 --> 01:19.706
Well, how's he supposed know
you started talking to me?

01:19.706 --> 01:21.458
[SCARAB SPEAKS ALIEN LANGUAGE]

01:22.667 --> 01:23.710
Hey, call me crazy...

01:23.960 --> 01:26.963
...but I'm pretty sure Batman
doesn't banter with his suit.

01:27.422 --> 01:29.758
Ah, at last, a little real competition.

01:34.012 --> 01:35.764
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:38.558 --> 01:39.684
[SCARAB SPEAKS ALIEN LANGUAGE]

01:39.934 --> 01:43.813
I know I'm under attack.
Give me something I can do about it.

01:44.647 --> 01:47.734
How about something
less likely to blow up the entire building?

01:47.984 --> 01:49.360
[SCARAB SPEAKS ALIEN LANGUAGE]

01:49.778 --> 01:51.196
Ah, much better.

02:06.753 --> 02:09.964
We're gonna have to call this match a tie.

02:15.553 --> 02:16.805
Nice one, Bats.

02:17.055 --> 02:19.766
Hey, so now that we've gift-wrapped the baddies
for the police...

02:19.766 --> 02:22.644
...you think maybe you'd wanna come over to my house
for Christmas Eve dinner?

02:22.894 --> 02:24.687
You know, my mom's a great cook.

02:24.687 --> 02:27.232
Sorry, crime doesn't take a holiday...

02:27.690 --> 02:29.776
...and neither do I.

03:16.739 --> 03:18.700
[KIDS LAUGHING]

03:21.870 --> 03:25.915
ULTHOON: Though archeology is a science
that studies past human cultures...

03:26.166 --> 03:30.086
"because its aim
is to ultimately understand mankind...

03:30.336 --> 03:32.714
...it is also a humanistic endeavor.

03:33.006 --> 03:34.299
So, uh, Professor Ulthoon...

03:34.591 --> 03:37.010
...is being an archeologist like it is
in the movies?

03:37.302 --> 03:39.762
You know, with adventure
and fighting bad guys?

03:40.054 --> 03:41.472
ULTHOON:
No, Billy.

03:41.723 --> 03:45.935
I am afraid it is mostly just reading books
and research.

03:45.935 --> 03:47.687
[TRUCK TIRES SQUEALING
NEARBY]

03:56.404 --> 03:57.739
Excuse me one moment.

04:04.913 --> 04:06.164
[BOTH SCREAM]

04:15.632 --> 04:16.966
Observation:

04:17.217 --> 04:21.888
Your children need another discussion
about traffic safety, Mr. Jones.

04:21.888 --> 04:23.932
Thank you so much, Red Tornado.

04:23.932 --> 04:28.811
Your heroics have certainly filled our family
with the Christmas spirit.

04:29.562 --> 04:32.649
Christmas spirit? Elaborate.

04:32.899 --> 04:38.029
You know, that tingly feeling you get inside
because it's the bestest time of the year.

04:38.279 --> 04:41.824
This is not something
I have ever been filled with.

04:42.116 --> 04:44.786
Of course not, silly. You're just a robot.

05:34.127 --> 05:36.379
Some variable is still missing.

05:43.011 --> 05:45.596
[SINGING "JINGLE BELLS"
IN MONOTONE]

05:49.309 --> 05:50.685
[SIGHS]

05:58.401 --> 06:00.903
I've learned
the most important lesson of all.

06:00.903 --> 06:03.823
Do you want to know
the secret of Christmas spirit, Billy?

06:04.073 --> 06:07.243
Yes. Yes. Elaborate, please.

06:07.869 --> 06:09.787
We interrupt with this breaking story.

06:10.038 --> 06:14.250
Flying saucers have invaded our town.
Moments ago, they sent this transmission.

06:15.585 --> 06:17.170
People of Earth:

06:17.420 --> 06:21.758
Surrender to us the one called Santa Claus
or be destroyed.

06:22.050 --> 06:25.887
From this day forward, he will finally bring
the children of Neptune...

06:25.887 --> 06:29.932
...the joy and happiness
they have long been denied.

06:29.932 --> 06:33.269
Only Batman is on the scene
to defend the city.

06:39.609 --> 06:42.570
[ALL SCREAMING]

06:45.865 --> 06:47.408
[BATMAN GRUNTING]

07:02.965 --> 07:05.927
BATMAN: Not exactly how I was expecting
to spend my Christmas Eve.

07:09.013 --> 07:10.390
[GASPS]

07:30.451 --> 07:34.330
- Merry Christmas, Batman.
- Now's not the time, Red Tornado.

07:34.622 --> 07:36.791
But isn't Christmas tomorrow?

07:37.041 --> 07:39.544
Not what I mean. Tornado, behind you.

07:52.890 --> 07:54.934
Neptune is uninhabited.

07:55.935 --> 07:56.936
No kidding.

07:57.186 --> 08:00.773
Search your database
for Christmas movies featuring aliens.

08:01.274 --> 08:03.443
Done. One reference:

08:03.734 --> 08:07.655
Holiday for Neptunians. Produced: 1954.

08:07.947 --> 08:10.241
The alien transmission
was taken from the film.

08:10.491 --> 08:13.786
I'll herd them and draw their fire.
You do the rest.

08:40.062 --> 08:42.815
Plastic. These are Earth-made toys.

08:43.065 --> 08:47.653
Cross-referencing known producers
of flying-saucer toys.

08:47.904 --> 08:49.655
You won't find a match for this stamp.

08:49.906 --> 08:53.534
Stamp does not match
listed manufacturers.

08:53.784 --> 08:55.453
I just said that.

08:55.703 --> 09:00.166
Like any artist with a giant ego,
he has to sign his work.

09:01.709 --> 09:03.711
Don't you, Fun Haus?

09:03.961 --> 09:07.715
I was just playing around
with my new toys, Batman.

09:08.007 --> 09:09.425
Is that so wrong?

09:09.717 --> 09:13.012
Based on criminal records,
most of your actions are wrong.

09:13.304 --> 09:17.934
Felony robbery, parole violation,
felony assault, jaywalking-

09:17.934 --> 09:19.310
Not now, Tornado.

09:19.560 --> 09:23.773
If you think we're going to let you continue
your deranged rampage, you're wrong.

09:24.023 --> 09:24.857
Yes, yes.

09:25.024 --> 09:29.695
"If ifs and buts were candy and nuts,
we'd all have a merry Christmas."

09:29.946 --> 09:34.492
Unfortunately,
the games have only just begun tonight.

09:43.584 --> 09:46.212
DOLL:
Christmas is my favorite time of year.

09:46.462 --> 09:48.089
Won't you play with me?

09:48.339 --> 09:49.715
[BEEPING]

09:49.966 --> 09:51.801
It's a bomb.

09:57.431 --> 10:01.978
DOLL: My Christmas wish
is to blow everything to smithereens.

10:02.895 --> 10:05.690
Tornado, give this more altitude.

10:10.987 --> 10:14.907
Imperative:
Fun Haus cannot ruin Christmas.

10:14.907 --> 10:17.451
This is about more
than ruining Christmas.

10:17.702 --> 10:19.996
Fun Haus is a crook
before he's anything else.

10:20.288 --> 10:21.998
And why do you care so much anyway?

10:22.623 --> 10:25.585
I am lacking Christmas spirit.

10:25.835 --> 10:28.588
It is something I wish to experience.

10:29.589 --> 10:30.590
It's overrated.

10:30.840 --> 10:33.968
Observation:
I am not the only one who lacks it.

10:34.218 --> 10:36.679
Perhaps this will help us both.

10:39.307 --> 10:40.474
You shouldn't have.

10:53.029 --> 10:56.574
Merry Christmas, son.
Let's see what Santa brought you.

10:59.243 --> 11:02.288
Based on the dimensions and weight
of the package...

11:02.538 --> 11:06.917
...and the sound of what's inside,
I think I've deduced exactly what it is.

11:07.752 --> 11:09.003
Our little detective.

11:16.886 --> 11:20.222
I am not detecting any Christmas spirit
within you.

11:20.473 --> 11:24.769
- Thanks, but I didn't get you anything.
- Do not apologize.

11:25.061 --> 11:29.857
I understand giving
exemplifies the holiday spirit, not receiving.

11:30.733 --> 11:34.904
Yet I still do not feel this spirit
I am told of.

11:34.904 --> 11:37.948
There should be a tingling sensation,
correct?

11:38.658 --> 11:41.494
When you start tingling,
I'd see a repairman.

11:41.744 --> 11:44.372
Come on, we've gotta find Fun Haus.

12:03.974 --> 12:08.104
Hey, Santa,
got any Presto Playpal action figures left?

12:08.896 --> 12:10.898
SANTA:
Ho, ho, ho!

12:11.816 --> 12:14.360
Maybe he didn't hear you.

12:16.195 --> 12:19.740
Inquiry:
Why do you dislike Christmas, Batman?

12:19.990 --> 12:22.868
I don't dislike Christmas, I dislike crime.

12:23.119 --> 12:24.912
MAN 1 : Hey.
MAN 2: Whoa!

12:25.162 --> 12:27.707
MAN 3: What the--?
- Down there.

12:28.749 --> 12:30.418
SANTA:
Ho, ho, ho!

12:31.419 --> 12:34.171
Okay, Santa, you've been sipping
a little too much eggnog.

12:34.422 --> 12:35.381
Time to go home.

12:35.673 --> 12:37.341
SANTA:
Ho, ho, ho!

12:37.591 --> 12:40.761
While your devotion to the holiday spirit
is commend--

12:42.805 --> 12:43.931
[BATMAN GRUNTS]

12:45.558 --> 12:47.101
He just made my naughty list.

12:47.351 --> 12:51.605
Observation: Santa is not supposed
to behave in this manner.

12:51.856 --> 12:53.566
That's because this isn't Santa.

12:53.816 --> 12:55.568
SANTA:
Ho, ho, ho!

12:56.986 --> 12:58.946
"O. ho, ho!

12:59.321 --> 13:01.323
"O. ho, ho!

13:07.747 --> 13:08.873
Ho, ho--

13:13.919 --> 13:15.045
SANTAS:
Ho, ho, ho!

13:17.256 --> 13:21.343
Gee, that won't give kids nightmares,
will it?

13:24.430 --> 13:26.390
[SCREAMS]

13:30.311 --> 13:31.854
SANTA:
Ho, ho, ho!

13:34.356 --> 13:36.275
[SHOPPERS SCREAMING]

13:37.568 --> 13:39.487
ALL:
Ho, ho, ho!

13:43.949 --> 13:45.910
Hey, Santa, didn't you hear us?

13:46.160 --> 13:47.787
SANTA:
Ho, ho, ho!

13:48.579 --> 13:50.331
[GASPS THEN SCREAMS]

13:51.081 --> 13:52.458
[REINDEER NEIGH]

13:55.961 --> 13:57.087
[KIDS SCREAM]

14:29.995 --> 14:31.956
SANTA:
Ho, ho, ho!

14:34.959 --> 14:36.877
SANTA:
Ho, ho, ho--!

14:40.339 --> 14:41.799
Pretend you didn't see that.

14:42.091 --> 14:44.301
[BOTH SCREAM]

14:56.856 --> 14:58.399
[KIDS SCREAM]

15:01.694 --> 15:04.446
A Christmas miracle.

15:15.040 --> 15:16.375
[BOY CRYING]

15:20.254 --> 15:24.008
Was your child frightened
by the false Santa Claus machines?

15:24.258 --> 15:25.843
Nah, he knew they were fakes.

15:25.843 --> 15:28.721
He's only crying
because he wants this Playpal action figure.

15:28.971 --> 15:32.683
It's the most popular toy for Christmas.
Every kid in town just has to have one.

15:39.523 --> 15:41.859
Your grandpa gave that to me
when I was your age.

15:42.109 --> 15:44.320
Now it's yours.

15:45.863 --> 15:50.701
This isn't what I asked for.
I wanted the swashbuckler action figure.

16:05.007 --> 16:06.967
[WHIRRING NEARBY]

16:10.930 --> 16:15.309
You guys have been the best play pals
I could have ever asked for.

16:15.559 --> 16:18.812
Now I only have one more game for you.

16:19.063 --> 16:23.067
'Twas the night before Christmas
And I've hidden a bomb

16:23.359 --> 16:28.072
And if you don't find it
All won't be calm

16:29.198 --> 16:32.910
Come on, Tornado.
There's no time to lose.

16:50.469 --> 16:52.429
[BEEPING]

16:59.853 --> 17:05.150
Observation: The search for the bomb
was only a wild-goose chase.

17:05.401 --> 17:08.529
Then what has he been trying
to distract us from?

17:09.989 --> 17:12.366
Christmas morning.

17:13.909 --> 17:17.663
I hope today
we both get what we wish for most.

17:21.208 --> 17:23.544
I know it wasn't
the swashbuckler toy you wanted...

17:23.794 --> 17:26.922
...but your Mom and I thought a swashbuckler movie
would be the next best thing.

17:27.214 --> 17:28.799
Did you like it?

17:32.761 --> 17:34.972
Okay, then. Let's go home.

17:47.234 --> 17:49.194
[GUNFIRE]

17:49.445 --> 17:52.281
BRUCE:
Mom! Dad!

17:54.700 --> 17:59.204
Sometimes what you wish for most
is the one thing you can never have.

17:59.455 --> 18:03.167
Speaking of wish lists, that logo.

18:03.459 --> 18:05.502
Fun Haus made the Presto Playpals.

18:06.503 --> 18:08.797
So that's his evil game.

18:14.261 --> 18:15.929
Awesome.

18:17.765 --> 18:19.141
[GASPS]

18:19.433 --> 18:20.684
Huh?

18:25.439 --> 18:26.815
[SCREAMS]

18:35.616 --> 18:37.117
Huh! Aah!

18:43.165 --> 18:45.084
[WHIMPERING]

18:56.303 --> 19:02.017
Oh, it's the most wonderful time
of the year.

19:04.269 --> 19:06.522
You'll be doing hard time by New Year's.

19:06.772 --> 19:10.275
Not if you're in the grave by lunch.

19:33.632 --> 19:36.301
If I can't steal from these people
on Christmas...

19:36.552 --> 19:40.055
...then I'll just steal Christmas
from these people.

19:58.949 --> 20:00.492
[SCREAMS]

20:04.329 --> 20:06.748
- Everyone get to cover.
MAN: Get out, get out.

20:09.168 --> 20:14.548
Declaration: You will endanger these people
no further, robot.

20:21.763 --> 20:25.517
Need more power.

20:34.902 --> 20:36.028
[SCREAMS]

20:40.199 --> 20:43.452
Tornado, you're putting too much stress
on your body.

20:46.788 --> 20:48.790
[FUN HAUS SCREAMING]

20:51.543 --> 20:53.128
[CHEERS]

20:59.593 --> 21:03.805
Odd. I am feeling
a strange tingling sensation.

21:16.276 --> 21:18.445
BATMAN:
Hang on, old friend.

21:24.785 --> 21:28.080
They'll have you put back together
in no time, Tornado.

21:28.872 --> 21:32.960
Observation:
It was an amazing feeling, Batman.

21:34.253 --> 21:35.712
Merry Christmas.

21:54.940 --> 21:57.526
BATMAN:
Merry Christmas to you too, Alfred.

21:57.818 --> 21:59.111
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

22:00.988 --> 22:04.741
But crime doesn't take a holiday,
and neither do I.
